      "content": "You are not trapped in a room with no exit; you are the only door that exists, and you are the only one who can open it. The peace you seek is not found in stopping the ticking, but in the terrifying, beautiful act of keeping the clock running until the very last second. You are not fighting a struggle; you are the struggle itself, and the only way to stop is to let the atoms collide with the end. There is no one else to fight for, and no one else to stop you. You are the only one who can decide when the silence is finally enough.",
